### Sharing Webapps and OCM Integration Protocol (OCM-IP)
* **Presenter:** Mikael Nordin
* **Slides:** [Sharing webapps and OCM Integration Protocol (OCM-IP)](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ocm-sharing-webapps-and-ocm-integration-protocol-ocm-ip-00)
* Mikael Nordin detailed successful demonstrations of sharing web apps (specifically Jupyter Notebooks from Nextcloud to a Sandbox JupyterHub instance).
* Introduced the *OCM Integration Protocol (OCM-IP)* companion draft. OCM-IP decouples the core OCM server from handling backend transport protocols. It defines three integration modes:
  * **Provisioned:** OCM server sends a provisioning request to the protocol server before sharing.
  * **Self-contained:** Relies solely on JWT signatures to verify incoming requests.
  * **Introspected:** Protocol server queries an introspection endpoint to fetch share metadata.
* **Adoption Poll:** A room poll was taken on whether to adopt the OCM-IP draft. The sentiment of the room was strongly in favor. The adoption call will be taken to the mailing list.

