### Use of OCM in the FileSender Platform
* **Presenter:** Guido Aben
* **Slides:** [Use of OCM in the FileSender platform](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ocm-use-of-ocm-in-the-filesender-platform-00)
* Guido Aben presented on FileSender, an open-source ad-hoc file transfer system widely used in the Research and Education (R&E) space.
* To support sovereign cloud storage, FileSender is adding capabilities to move files directly from cloud-to-cloud holdings (e.g., Nextcloud or ownCloud) instead of uploading from local user devices.
* Implementing OCM allows FileSender to tap into a large, established catchment area of personal cloud deployments.
* FileSender will separate upload and deposit control planes using OCM invitation and transfer flows, allowing for automated deposits into trusted research environments. This implementation is funded for the coming year, and development insights will be fed back to the working group.

